This file contains the commands used in the PKI LAB.
This will help with cut and Paste.
****** Generate a Self-Signed Certificate ********
openssl req -new -x509 -keyout ca.key -out ca.crt -config openssl.cnf

***** Generate public/private key pair *****************
openssl genrsa -aes128 -out server.key 1024

****** View server key *********************
openssl rsa -in server.key –text | more

****** Generate a Certificate Signing Request (CSR).  *****
openssl req -new -key server.key -out server.csr -config openssl.cnf

***** Generating Certificates ***************
openssl ca -in server.csr -out server.crt -cert ca.crt -keyfile ca.key -config openssl.cnf

***** View the Certificate. ********************
You can view the new certificate with the following command. Run from your HOME Directory.
openssl x509 -in server.crt –text |more

********* Deploy and Start Apache ***********************
sudo a2enmod ssl             {Enable the SSL module}
sudo a2ensite seed-ssl      {Enable the site}
sudo service apache2 restart {Restart Apache}
